{"key":"processedPost-12914529","value":{"id":12914529,"first":12913571,"last":12914529,"when":1279460542,"utime":"07/18/10 04:42 PM","content":"Personally, I disagree strongly with attempts to automate a terrarium, especially by new growers just learning the ropes.&nbsp; <br />When you mist a few times daily, it gives a chance to really inspect the substrate for any sign of mold.&nbsp; If you automate it, you might go too long without looking and find the darned thing covered with mold, puking trillions of trichoderma spores into your growing area.&nbsp; Misting by hand also lets you read each substrate and determine exactly how much to mist.<br />As already said, the MMGG is outdated, but was crappy at best ten years ago.&nbsp; Fruiting parameters for mushrooms haven't changed in thousands of years. . .we just know a lot more about them now.<br />RR","title":"Re: Not managing to increase humidity inside terrarium (Ultrasonic Fogger)"}}